left_text: All tagmata richly marked with yellow; mandible of female with median tooth longer than others; maxillary palpus 5-segmented; gonobase of male nearly as long as midventral length of gonocoxite
right_text: Body dark except for clypeus and limited pale marks elsewhere (thus coloration as in most Braunsapis); mandible of female with lower tooth longer than others; maxillary palpus 6-segmented; gonobase much shorter than midventral length of gonocoxite
